skill.dss.ending_blow.hud.success=FATALITY
skill.dss.leaping_blow.name=Leaping Blow
skill.dss.leaping_blow.activation=[Sword]\nHold block and jump into the air, then attack to perform a leaping slash. Shield is not required. More effective using higher ground.
skill.dss.leaping_blow.description=A powerful technique, the leaping blow is capable of striking and debilitating many foes at once. Enemies within the area of effect are weakened in addition to taking damage.\n\nTargets are affected based on their proximity to the center of the attack path; those further to the sides suffer less damage and a reduced weakness duration.\n\nDamage is calculated based on the attack bonus of the weapon used to perform the attack, plus bonus damage proportional to the skill level of the attacker.
skill.dss.leaping_blow.tooltip=A multi-target leaping slash
skill.dss.mortal_draw.name=Mortal Draw
skill.dss.mortal_draw.activation=[Sword] [Targeted]\nWhile empty-handed, hold the block key and press attack just as an enemy's strike is about to land; requires a sword to be in the hotbar.
skill.dss.mortal_draw.description=Battoujutsu, also known as the art of unsheathing or drawing the sword, is one of the most difficult and deadly skills to master.\n\nWhen executed properly, the incoming attack is not only entirely neutralized, but the attacker is left completely vulnerable to attack, allowing the sword master to strike with the utmost efficacy.\n\nA successful battoujutsu inflicts double damage to the target, including all enchantment bonuses. This skill cannot be used in quick succession, as the sword must be placed back in its sheath before it may again be drawn.
skill.dss.mortal_draw.tooltip=A devastating quick-draw sword technique
skill.dss.parry.name=Parry
skill.dss.parry.activation=Tap back, back, block just as the foe's strike is about to land. Shield is not required.
skill.dss.parry.description=Parrying is a fundamental defensive skill, even more powerful than blocking as it will completely negate damage when successful, as well as possibly disarming an attacker. The chance to disarm is affected greatly by timing, and is the sole deciding factor amongst opponents of equal skill.\n\nNote that it is impossible to parry natural attacks such as the feared zombie punch or creeper blast; only attacks with weapons or items may be parried.
